overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul of their sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent began by analyzing the existing visual
  design, identifying areas for improvement such as a generic color palette,
  plain backgrounds, and basic form elements. A new, calming sleep-themed color
  palette was introduced using deep indigos, purples, and teal accents. The main
  form layout was significantly redesigned with decorative background blurs, a
  polished progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern on card headers. All
  core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards received
  enhanced styling with improved hover states and visual feedback. The welcome
  screen was transformed into a more engaging hero section with feature cards.
  Consistent styling was then applied across all 14 questionnaire sections,
  replacing generic gray boxes with themed card-like groupings. A critical
  console error related to null values being passed to input components was also
  addressed. Finally, the agent refined the alert styling to align with the new
  theme and increased the border opacity of section grouping boxes for better
  visual definition. The overall outcome is a much more polished, cohesive, and
  professional application that evokes a sense of calm appropriate for a sleep
  health questionnaire.
